          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript employed for consultation and recitation; praises the month of Mārgaśīrṣa (November-December), when the moon enters into the constellation of Mṛgaśiras. Presented as a conversation between the Hindu deities Kṛṣṇa and Brahmā.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Mārgaśīrṣamāhātmya</title>
              <title type="vernacular">मार्गशीर्षमाहात्म्य</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>former owner</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Mauni, Bālaṃbhaṭa</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīskaṃdapurāṇe mārgaśīrṣamāhātmye ṣoḍśodhyāyā 16 mārgaśīrṣamāhātmasaṃpūrṇam astu / śrīkāśiviśveśvarārpaṇam astu saṃvat 1876 śake 1741 vikrutināmasa[ṃ]vatsare pauṣakṛṣṇa 13 somyavāsare / (f. 43v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
